divs: Sighting DetailsIn late May of this year I was taking pictures while walking my dog in a field in rural Illinois. After taking the pictures I shelved the camera until my next outing. I always have a camera on my walks to take shots of my dogs and in nice settings and of anything else I may run across. Father's Day my wife had purchased me a new camera so there the camera sat for 2 months. Well I finally dusted off the old camera the other day and decided to get the pictures off of it to add to my albums. When I was looking at one of the pictures I took I noticed a object in the corner of the picture. I blew it up and can not identify it. I have had the Illinois Audubon society look at it and they tell me it is not a bird. I've had a meterologist take a look to ensure it is not a weather balloon. I have even asked someone I know in law enforcement about the possiblility of it being a unmanned drone for marijuanna plant detection and they assured me that my area had none of those. Would it be possible to have someone take a look to see if you can identify what this may be? I know what it looks like at first glance, but I would like your opinion on this. This is a cropped version of the original picture and has been enlarged. If you would like a copy of the original please let me know. Thank You for your time, Richard Bonnett
Summary: reviewing photo of my dog and discovered the object in the upper portion of the photo
